With an undergraduate enrollment of approximately 2200 students, Muhlenberg College is dedicated to shaping creative, compassionate, collaborative leaders through rigorous academic programs in the arts, humanities, natural sciences and social sciences as well as selected pre-professional programs, including accounting, business, education and public health. A member of the Centennial Conference, Muhlenberg competes in 22 varsity sports. Muhlenberg is affiliated with the Evangelical Lutheran Church in America.

A world lived together with a designed one, but one that speaks with emotion about loneliness and multiplication of her tracks in a world that herself loses increasingly more.

data.name: BMX Trick Challenge 2012 Highlights
data.description:
BMX TRICK CHALLENGE 2012
 
15.09. 2012 we have organized bmx trick challenge contest in Domžale. Most of Slovenian bmx riders had came and also a few from  Austria.  The  weather was great, sunny and warm and a lot of wievers and bmx fans came, and they enjoyed good music and good bmx riding.
There were two tipes of tricks to ride, banger tricks and combo tricks. The winners under 16 years got practical prizes and the winners over 16 years got  money check worth 50 eur and practical prizes  per challenge as well.
 
There were 7 contestants under 16 years, who were in the battle to win challenges. Two challenges won Matej Žan and two challenges won Blaž Godina, and one challenge was won over Jože Podbregar.
 
And for the contestants over 16 years there was 20 riders battleing for the prizes. The absolute best one was Rok Krivec, who has showed once again his incredible tech skills, he won 3 challenges, almoust four. The next two challenges were won over Domen Fekonja, and one challenge each were won over Davor Jug, Miha Fištravec, Žiga Krebl, Nik Pušnik and Daniel Juritsch, who has won  bunny hop challenge (115 cm).
 
After the awards ceremony there was evening session under the lights, and for the finish there was after party with the good old disco music.

user.name: EZ3X
user.bio: Smo skupina mladih športnikov, ki se zavzema za izboljšanje pogojev na področju ekstremnih športov na lokalni ter regionalni ravni. Ideja, da se ustanovi športno društvo, je nastala že pred desetimi leti, a ni prišla do epiloga vse do leta 2005. Najbolj smo aktivni na domžalskem poligonu za adrenalinske športe, sodelujemo pa tudi pri podobnih projektih z mladinskimi organizacijami v Sloveniji. Med našimi člani so tudi državni prvaki in mednarodni tekmovalci, ki so že dosegali odlične rezultate na tovrstnih adrenalinskih tekmovanjih.

data.name: Carinhoso Lobisomem (Loving Werewolf)
data.description:
This is the videoclip of a music that I composed (dedicated to my wife, who loves dogs...) to use as theme song of a philosophy videoclasses serie in the internet, with the contents expressed in a very personalized way, with some dark humor and passages in surrealistic stile. It's in portuguese yet, without traduction for now, and presents a lot of flying texts not traducted too. I have not a good english, so sorry for this. The song is named "Carinhoso Lobisomem", that means something like "Loving Werewolf". The video begining with a provocative question writed in large tipes (if my bad english let me talk this correctly...): "Aren't ower thoughs made of myths?". 
This serie of philosophy videoclasses is a part of my site:
http://www.projetoquem.com.br
"Projeto quem" (in portuguese) we can traduct project-who (philosophy can be usefull to construct personality... that's the idea).
You can find this video in the site, in my Facebook (João Borba) or in Daily Motion too.

data.name: ESCALARPA -architactural string instrument
data.description:
ESCALARPA
 
Escalarpa is a sound installation and a musical instrument at the same time.
It was originally created in 2004 for the exposition 9 Jocs d'Art (9 art games) at the Art  Museum of Sabadell (BCN, Spain).
 
A set of metal strings is mounted and tensed through the space of a stairway. Each string is amplified by mean of a piezo microphone, The sound is processed by a computer and/or by a set of programmable effects (basically modulation and delay).
 
Visitors can walk inside the instrument and play (with) it. Musician can play and compose for ESCALARPA also in combination with other instruments. A particulary dynamic sound can be obtained by using bows.
 
ESCALARPA is a social, adaptable and  light thing.
It is a social instrument, it is widely adaptable to different tipes of stairways and to other structures (artificial and natural). It is easy and compact to carry, install, and eventually replicate.

data.name: Tipping Points – Peter Ditlevsen
data.description:
”På et tidspunkt når du et punkt, hvor du er gået over til en anden tilstand. Vi skulle gerne undgå, at det sker i klimaet, for det kan føre til nogle meget dramatiske klimaforandringer i en hastighed, vi slet ikke er vant til.”

Jordens vand, is, luft, jord og levende organismer er vævet sammen i ét stort, kompleks system. Men en pludselig ændring i en del af systemet kan få det til at tippe.

Tipping points er et begreb for det, mange af os er begyndt at forstå: at klimaet kan tippe. Peter Ditlevsen er fysiker og forsker i, hvordan vi fysisk og matematisk kan beskrive disse pludselig skift eller omvæltninger, hvor en del af eller hele klimasystemet går over i en ny tilstand.

Ditlevsen er leder af et stort, internationalt forskningsprojekt, der skal identificere de vigtigste tipping points og undersøge, hvordan man kan integrere dem i klimamodellerne. For at udvikle deres teori om tipping points holder Ditlevsen og hans kollegaer derfor især øje med den smeltende is, havstrømmene i Atlanten, den tøende permafrost og med, om regnskoven måske holder op med at regne på sig selv.

Det er en stor udfordring at kombinere fysikkens enkle teorier med de komplekse og datatunge klimamodeller. For spørgsmålet er, om vi allerede har nået et eller flere tipping points, der forandrer havstrømmene eller får regnskoven til at tørre ud? Og hvad sker der, hvis en del af systemet vælter? Kan det føre en kaskade af tipping points  med sig?

Peter Ditlevsen er lektor i fysik ved Niels Bohr Institutet og leder af forskningscenteret TiPES – Tipping Points in the Earth System.

data.name: Neries regata 2009 (trailer)
data.description:
Tūkstančio laivų regata

„1000 metų – 1000 laivų"– su tokiu šūkiu startavo renginys "Tūkstančio laivų regata".
2009 metais Lietuva švenčia savo vardo tūkstantmetį, o Vilnius tapo Europos kultūros sostine. Pažymėti šiuos du istorinius įvykius pakvietėme visus Lietuvos gyventojus ir svečius. 7 kilometrus Nerimi, nuo Valakupių iki Baltojo tilto, plaukė 1000 laivų. Vienas laivas vieneriems Lietuvos valstybės istorijos metams pažymėti.
„Tūkstančio laivų regatoje" galėjo dalyvauti visų tipų ir konstrukcijų laivai: baidarės, kanojos, irklinės valtys, luotai, vandens dviračiai, geldos, plaustai, savadarbės irklinės priemonės - visa kas laikosi ant vandens ir varoma žmogaus raumenų jėga. Tai įspūdingas reginys žiūrovams, susirinkusiems ant Neries krantinių, tiltų ir į aikštę prie Baltojo tilto. O regatos dalyviams nepakartojama proga dalyvauti istorijoje ir patiems ją kurti. Kita tokia proga bus tik po tūkstančio metų.
Visi dalyviai gavo atminimo suvenyrus.

Renginio kulminacija – tradicinės kasmetinės tarptautinės „Neries regata" Universitetų komandų rungtynės. „Tūkstančio laivų regatoje" komandos varžėsi originaliais vikingų laivais, kurių komandą susideda iš 7 porų irklininkų, būgnininko ir vairininko.
1000 laivų Neryje, Vilniuje – tai unikalus faktas, kurį sieksime užfiksuoti Lietuvos rekordų knygoje. Dalyvių ekipažų skaičius ribotas - 1000 sertifikuotų laivų – nei vienu daugiau, nei vienu mažiau, todėl vyko tik išankstinė dalyvių registracija.

neriesregata.lt


"Thousand ships regatta"
"1000 years - 1000 ships" - "Thousand ships regatta" will start with such slogan.
In 2009 Lithuania will celebrate it's name thousand years anniversary and Vilnius will become Europe's cultural capital. We will invite all Lithuanian citizens and guests to celebrate these two events. 1000 ships will sail 7 km by Neris river from Valakampiai bridge down to White bridge. One ship for one year of history of Lithuania.
All tipes and construction ships will have possibility to participate in "Thousand ships regatta": cayaks, canoes, paddle ships, skiffs, water bycicles, trouhs, rafts, hand made floating devices - all what can float on water and is driven by man power. This will be impressive event for spectators that will gather on Neris river banks, bridges and square next to White bridge. For regatta participants this will be unique possibility to be part of historical event and create history themselves. Another such opportunity will be one thousand years later only. All participants will get remembrance souvenirs.

Culmination of the event - traditional international every year University teams competition "Neries regata". University teams will compete in original vikings ships, which team consists from 7 pairs of paddlers, drummer and helmsman.
1000 ships on Neris river - unique fact, which we will aim to fix in Lithuanian record book. Number of participants crews is limited - 1000 certified ships - no one more, no one less, therefor only advance registration will be accepted.
